.TH "lpfc_max_rpi_show" 9 "lpfc_max_rpi_show" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
lpfc_max_rpi_show \- Return maximum rpi
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "ssize_t" lpfc_max_rpi_show
.BI "(struct device *dev "  ","
.BI "struct device_attribute *attr "  ","
.BI "char *buf "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev" 12
class device that is converted into a Scsi_host.
.IP "attr" 12
device attribute, not used.
.IP "buf" 12
on return contains the maximum rpi count in decimal or "Unknown".
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Calls \fBlpfc_get_hba_info\fP asking for just the mrpi count.
If \fBlpfc_get_hba_info\fP returns zero (failure) the buffer text is set
to "Unknown" and the buffer length is returned, therefore the caller
must check for "Unknown" in the buffer to detect a failure.
.SH "RETURN"
size of formatted string.
